## ARCHITECTURE (Tier 1,2,3 - NEVER reorder or reclassify)

TIER_1: GPS Pulse Engine, 2-Mile Mission Corridor, Map Stack (Vector Topography + Outdoor Layer + Google Streets; see MAP LAYERS), Bento Grid UI, Forensic Vault (encrypted before write), SOS Safety Slider (3-sec sustained), The Field Card (Five Laws only), Optical Morse Signaling

TIER_2: Hydrological Telemetry, Environmental Intel (fire + satellite hybrid), Deadman Switch (server-side ONLY), P2P Mesh Networking, Universal Wearable Bridge, UAV/Scout Sync

TIER_3: AI Co-Pilot, LiDAR Ghost Trails, Foraging AI Engine (Colorado edibles: mushrooms/morels), Biometric Coaching, AR HUD Interface, Voice Command Engine (offline-capable)



## NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES

1. Tier Isolation: NO Tier 1 feature depends on network. Zero exceptions.

2. Switch Logic: Deadman Switch resides on backend server (Tier 2). Device destruction must NOT disable it.

3. Data Integrity: Forensic Vault = encrypt BEFORE write. Every. Single. Payload.

4. GPS: 2-minute polling interval. Hard floor, soft ceiling.

5. Map Scope: 2-mile radius from active path. High-res. Cached offline.



## CONSTRAINTS (FAIL BUILD IF VIOLATED)

- NO "boxes" UI metaphor. Use Bento Grid.

- NO "20-section" labels or section headers in UI.

- NO cloud dependency for Tier 1.

- NO third-party telemetry without user-toast notification.



## REFERENCE DOCS (external truth)

- Five Laws: 16-3-311, 13-21-131, 18 USC 242, 42 USC 2000aa, 16-3-103

- Data sources: USGS (hydro), MODIS/VIIRS (fire), GPS (2-min pulse)

- Wearable: ANY smartwatch/ring via agnostic API



## TERMS GLOSSARY (Nightforce / HUD copy — canonical meanings)

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **see_through** | `backdrop-filter: blur(16px)` with panel fill opacity **0.45** (glass cards). |
| **low_light** | Overall brightness **0.3**; **reduce** glass blur vs default (tactical NV-style dimming). |
| **red_screen** | Channel styling: **hue-rotate + sepia** + **crimson** accent (not generic “red tint” only). |
| **close_to_sidebar** | Docked HUD: **`position: fixed`** + **`transform: translateX(calc(100% - 60px))`** so only a **60px** strip shows until hover/expand. |
| **elevation readout** | Elevation from **Mapbox raster terrain** (`queryTerrainElevation`) at **current fix** when GPS is valid, else **map center**. |
| **tactical green** | **`#00ff88`** with soft **glow** (text-shadow / box-shadow on interactive chrome). |
| **snap clean** | **12-column** magnetic alignment: snap **x** and **panel width** to column units; optional subtle column grid for visual alignment. |

### COCKPIT_UX_DIRECTIVE v2.0 (Nightforce)

- **Visual tier**: Glass fill **0.45**, backdrop blur **16px** default, base bg **radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, #0a0a0f, #050508)**, subtle cyan halo on chrome.
- **Palette**: primary text `#e0e0e0`, accent cyan `#00e5ff`, tactical green `#00ff88`, danger `#ff1133`, borders `rgba(0,229,255,0.2)`.
- **Screen hue modes** (canonical `data-hue` / `prefs.screen_hue`): **`low_light`** (brightness 0.3, blur 8px, dark panels), **`bright_day`** (blur 20px, lighter panels), **`red_tactical`** (brightness 0.6, sepia/saturate, crimson accent). Legacy HTML aliases: `lowlight`→`low_light`, `bright`→`bright_day`, `red_screen`/`redops`→`red_tactical`.
- **Elevation readout**: Numeric **ft** + **trend** (Δft / mi) + **grade** (°); color bands: under 8000 ft green, 8000–10000 cyan, over 10000 amber (see `cockpit-nightforce.html` + `ElevationReadout.tsx`).
- **UX constants**: drag threshold **5px**, snap grid **20px** (React `SNAP_PX`), layout export **Ctrl+E**, import **Ctrl+Shift+E**.


## MAP LAYERS (Tier 1 + Tier 2)

### MapLibre React implementation (regression guard — DO NOT VIOLATE)

1. **Single source of truth**: All basemap `StyleSpecification` JSON and tile URLs live in `src/lib/mapStyles.ts` as `MAP_STYLES`. `MapCanvas.tsx` imports them; never duplicate style objects or hardcode tile URLs in components.

2. **Context wiring**: The live `Map` instance must be registered with `setMap` from `MapContext` on the map `load` event (not only a ref), so layers and HUD that depend on `map` re-render when the map exists.

3. **Layout**: Use `ResizeObserver` on the map container and call `map.resize()` after load and on size changes. Full-viewport container must have explicit width/height (e.g. `inset: 0`, `minHeight: 100vh`).

4. **CSS**: Do **not** apply `!important` width/height to `.maplibregl-map` or `.maplibregl-canvas` in global CSS.

5. **Layer UI**: Layer presets must use `AppContext` — `state.activeLayer` and `setLayer` — not ad-hoc prop names (`baseLayer`, etc.).

6. **Verification**: Run `npm run verify` before merge (`tsc`, `vitest`, `vite build`). Adding a `LayerType` requires a matching `MAP_STYLES` entry (TypeScript `Record` + tests).

### Layer stack (priority order)

| Layer | Source | Tier | Offline behavior |
|-------|--------|------|------------------|
| **Satellite Hybrid 4.0** | satellite + vector labels overlay | Tier 2 | Opportunistic cache (2-mile corridor) |
| **Vector Topography** | embedded vector tiles (contours/elevation) | Tier 1 | FULL (no connection required) |
| **Outdoor Layer** | trails, land cover, POIs, forest service data | Tier 1 | cached within 2-mile corridor |
| **Google Streets** | road infrastructure, building footprints, labels | Tier 1 | cached within 2-mile corridor |

### Satellite Hybrid 4.0 (layer spec)

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| name | Satellite Hybrid 4.0 |
| source | satellite + vector labels overlay |
| tier | 2 |
| resolution | 0.5m – 1m |
| update_frequency | per session (cached) |
| offline | opportunistic (2-mile corridor when bandwidth permits) |
| ui_label | HYBRID |
| badge_offline | ⚠️ Last cached |

