- Tier 2: network-dependent, cached fallbacks, must not break Tier 1

- Tier 3: mock-first, no paid/real AI APIs in v1, must not break Tiers 1–2



## RELEASE v1.0.0 (2026-05-04)



Unified stack: **`src/tier3-intelligence.html`** (Tier 1 + Tier 2 + Tier 3). Standalone tiers: `src/tier1-hud.html`, `src/tier2-connectivity.html`.



### Features

- **Tier 1:** GPS (2 min poll), SOS (3 s sustained slide), Forensic Vault (encrypt before write), Field Card (five laws), Bento Grid UI

- **Tier 2:** Deadman Switch (mock POST heartbeat), USGS hydrological telemetry, environmental MODIS/VIIRS-style mock, connection status bar

- **Tier 3:** AI Co-Pilot (hazard reroute mock), LiDAR ghost trails (canvas path mock), biometric coaching (HR zones), Foraging AI (seasonal text mock), AR HUD placeholder (Viture/XREAL), voice commands (Web Speech + typed fallback)



### Known Limitations (v1)

- LiDAR is a 2D canvas mock (true 3D would need e.g. Three.js).

- Foraging AI is text-only (no image recognition).

- AR HUD is a placeholder until eyewear is paired.

- Web Speech API typically requires HTTPS or localhost.

- Deadman Switch uses a mock POST only (no production backend in-repo).



### Validation

- Tier isolation and `.cursorrules` constraints verified for v1.

- Hash-verified drift protection: Tier 1 and Tier 2 file hashes recorded above; re-hash after intentional edits.

